    <p>The <xref href="carrier-grade-install-kvm-esx-GA.dita#topic10581cgikeg">process for installing the
                KVM + ESX deployment</xref> requires several JSON files that will be used when
            deploying the HLM VM.</p>
<section id="sample-node-provisionjson-file">
  <p>The following represents a sample <codeph>machine_architecture.json</codeph> file in the
                    <codeph>/opt/share/hlm/1/site/</codeph> directory of the HLM VM for <xref
                    href="carrier-grade-install-pb-overview.dita#topic1925/nic">a bonded NIC
                    installation</xref>. Use values appropriate for your environment.</p>
            <p>Return to <xref href="carrier-grade-install-kvm-esx-GA.dita#topic10581cgikeg">Installing
                    the KVM + ESX Deployment</xref>.</p>
        
<codeblock>{
                    "name": "ProLiant DL360 Gen9",
                    "model-class": "001",
                    "port": [
                        {
                            "name": "port1",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:1c.4/0000:02:00.0"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port2",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:1c.4/0000:02:00.1"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port3",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:1c.4/0000:02:00.2"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port4",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:1c.4/0000:02:00.3"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port5",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:02.2/0000:04:00.0"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port6",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:02.2/0000:04:00.1"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port7",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:02.0/0000:05:00.0"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port8",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:02.0/0000:05:00.1"
                        }
}</codeblock>
    
    
    <p> NOTE: The configuration processor assigns the first address of the CLM address range to itself for serving python 
        and debian repositories. Make sure that you set the first IP address of the CLM range for the eth2 (CLM) address of the HLM node.</p>
    
